(103310, 'ruRU', '', '<Li Li''s ears perk up.>$b$bWell, the story goes that there is this land covered by sand called Uldum.', 21154),
(103311, 'ruRU', 'I''ve also heard of it.', 'I''ve also heard of it.', 21154),
(103312, 'ruRU', 'I''ve been there before.', 'I''ve been there before.', 21154),
(103313, 'ruRU', '', 'Oh that''s so cool! I wish I could visit there sometime.$b$bSo according to the story thousands of years ago there was this smith called Irmaat who used to live there. The smith was known all throughout the land for his excellent work in creating magical weapons that represent the air spirits that live there.$b$bHis finest work was said to be a set of hand blades that were formed from the essence of pure air. The story goes on that he attempted to summon the lord of the winds to imbue the weapons with its power.$b$bThat didn''t go so well for him.', 21154),
(103314, 'ruRU', '', 'It''s supposed to be REALLY dry and covered all with sand like a big kitty box! I wish I could see it!$b$bSo according to the story thousands of years ago there was this smith called Irmaat who used to live there. The smith was known all throughout the land for his excellent work in creating magical weapons that represent the air spirits that live there.$b$bHis finest work was said to be a set of hand blades that were formed from the essence of pure air. The story goes on that he attempted to summon the lord of the winds to imbue the weapons with its power.$b$bThat didn''t go so well for him.', 21154),
(103315, 'ruRU', 'What happened then?', 'What happened then?', 21154),
(103316, 'ruRU', '', 'According to the story, the lord of air was filled with great wrath and decided to play a trick on Irmaat.$b$bThe lord of air imbued the weapons with the purest form of his essence, knowing that Irmaat could not possibly wield such power. Irmaat named his creation the "Fists of the Heavens" and held them to the sky to admire his work. This was a mistake, for when he did this it conjured a great vortex of swirling sand and air that was completely out of his control! The vortex scattered the smith''s blades and buried his home under the desert sands.$b$bWouldn''t it be neat if the blades were real? I''d give anything to get out of here and go search for them!', 21154),
