(108510, 'ruRU', '', 'What are you waiting for? Check out that noise!', 21154),
(108511, 'ruRU', '', 'There''s a great Nightborne banquet tonight, and we would like to serve up something... special. We need you to distract the chef.', 21154),
(108512, 'ruRU', '', 'You! Have a look over there!', 21154),
(108513, 'ruRU', '', 'Excellent! One of my agents added our special ingredient. Remember, banquets can be more perilous than battles.', 21154),
(108514, 'ruRU', '', 'Mortal flesh... so pretty when it burns!', 21154),
(108515, 'ruRU', '', 'I''m feeling positively radiant!', 21154),
(108516, 'ruRU', '', 'It will amuse me to watch you melt!', 21154),
(108517, 'ruRU', '', 'Who needs henchmen? I''ll burn you myself!', 21154),
(108518, 'ruRU', '', 'I believe my brother Mardranel is prepared to accompany you. Thank you for your help, friend.', 21154),
(108519, 'ruRU', 'You seek blessing? Blessing? Like... feather? Claw? Hm. I give this, yes. You help Feathermane first.', '', 21154),
(108520, 'ruRU', 'Yowlon purrs quietly.', '', 21154),
(108522, 'ruRU', 'Divine Shield protected you from the mage''s first attack, but the second attack has left you wounded. As a paladin your conviction allows you to heal yourself and your allies. Flash of Light is a cornerstone of your healing arsenal.', '', 21154),
(108523, 'ruRU', 'Use Flash of Light until all your health is restored.', '', 21154),
(108524, 'ruRU', 'If you want, I show you the way. If you don''t want, that good too. It is over water.', '', 21154),
(108525, 'ruRU', 'I had such high hopes for you. An amateur merchant believes that a partner is a valuably ally. A master knows that they are competition and a liability.', '', 21154),
(108526, 'ruRU', 'Strange, I was expecting my associate. No matter, you have led me to my goal. Too bad you will not live to see my rise to glory!', '', 21154),
(108527, 'ruRU', 'No! The designs... were mine...', '', 21154),
(108528, 'ruRU', 'This place is noisier than my tree! I will go back and get a feather for you. You tried. Sort of.', '', 21154),
(108529, 'ruRU', 'I am pleased. This one has earned the blessing of the Feathermane. I offer a feather from my mane.', '', 21154),
(108530, 'ruRU', 'Yowlon looks toward you and purrs quietly.', '', 21154),
(108531, 'ruRU', 'Come and play with my kittens again soon, $r.', '', 21154),
(108532, 'ruRU', 'Did you get the blessing? Oh- he''s BIG!', '', 21154),
(108533, 'ruRU', 'Mardranel points toward Yowlon.', '', 21154),
(108534, 'ruRU', 'Well. Seems that is in order. I believe Mythandros is ready for you to continue. Three blessings to go!', '', 21154),
(108535, 'ruRU', 'Hmmm... Your scent is unfamiliar. The one wearing trees on his body explained that you seek my blessing. I will consider it. First, you must assist my family.', '', 21154),
(108536, 'ruRU', 'I can smell the grass in the wind... it is sweet, and young. My family will eat well, and without worry of wolves! Thank you, friend. Accept my blessing.', '', 21154),
(108537, 'ruRU', 'Redhoof shakes his head vigorously, causing one antler to fall free.', '', 21154),
(108538, 'ruRU', 'It appears as though we have arrived, $n. Let us see what Celestos would have us do next.', '', 21154),
(108539, 'ruRU', 'I hope you will accept our offering of food and space, great Redhoof. It is our wish to share this land with you peacefully. Please give us your blessing.', '', 21154),
(108540, 'ruRU', ',          .', '', 21154),
(108541, 'ruRU', 'Startalon settles and tucks her head under her wing for a moment. She straightens again and offers a dry owl talon out to Mayruna.', '', 21154),
(108542, 'ruRU', 'Startalon dips her head in silent thanks and takes to the skies once more.', '', 21154),
(108543, 'ruRU', '', 'Thank you, moon child. May your sight stay keen.', 21154),
(108544, 'ruRU', 'Would you be able to repair this flask for me?', 'Would you be able to repair this flask for me?', 21154),
(108545, 'ruRU', 'Silverfang deposits a shiny, smooth Nightsaber Fang onto the dirt.', '', 21154),
(108546, 'ruRU', 'Silverfang lets out a low, passive growl before vanishing into the shadows from whence she came.', '', 21154),
