(110905, 'ruRU', 'Welcome, $p. Arms warriors are the ultimate physical combatants, using martial skill and weaponry to crush those who stand against them. But you cannot defeat an opponent that''s out of reach. Fortunately, you have a skill to solve this problem.', '', 21154),
(110906, 'ruRU', '"I''m hoping for some epic pants drops tonight."$b$bA wave of confusion washed over the princess''s face as the full force of this statement hit her square on. A murmur arose among her court. Lord Gravesbane heard weapons being drawn.$b$bThe princess''s eyebrows furrowed, and she said...$b$b|cFF600000<How might the draenei princess have responded?>|r', '', 21154),
(110907, 'ruRU', 'It is done. I will dispose of the ashes and find Mayruna back at camp. Thank you, friend.', '', 21154),
(110908, 'ruRU', 'Let me know if you want to rumble, $r.', 'Let me know if you want to rumble, $r.', 21154),
(110909, 'ruRU', 'Is that... Felo''melorn? The Flamestrike?', 'Is that... Felo''melorn? The Flamestrike?', 21154),
(110910, 'ruRU', 'It is. $n recovered it from Northrend. The very spellblade that Dath''Remar used against the Legion during the War of the Ancients.', 'It is. $n recovered it from Northrend. The very spellblade that Dath''Remar used against the Legion during the War of the Ancients.', 21154),
(110911, 'ruRU', 'Let us hope that the mages do not succumb to the Legion''s influence. We need their help.', 'Let us hope that the mages do not succumb to the Legion''s influence. We need their help.', 21154),
(110912, 'ruRU', 'Deception is punishable by death!', '', 21154),
(110913, 'ruRU', 'Fire the guns! Cover the path in Hellfire! Don''t let that Warlock through!', '', 21154),
(110914, 'ruRU', 'Yowlon hisses angrily at the sight of the Ettin Leather.', '', 21154),
(110915, 'ruRU', 'I''ll be taking that, friend. Don''t you worry.', '', 21154),
(110916, 'ruRU', 'Yowlon kneads his claws into the stone, looking regally in the other direction.', '', 21154),
(110917, 'ruRU', 'Thanks!', 'Thanks!', 21154),
(110918, 'ruRU', 'There! Your kittens are safe, Yowlon. Will you grant us your blessing so we may share this land with you?', '', 21154),
(110919, 'ruRU', 'Yowlon''s tail flicks. He offers a firm nod and tilts his head back to retrieve a feather from his mane.', '', 21154),
(110920, 'ruRU', 'Thank you, your highness.', '', 21154),
(110921, 'ruRU', 'Yowlon deposits the feather into Mardranel''s palm.', '', 21154),
(110922, 'ruRU', 'Without a Windlord, Skywall will forever remain in turmoil.', '', 21154),
(110923, 'ruRU', 'There is no Windlord, Farseer. The lesser lords endlessly battle for power.', '', 21154),
(110924, 'ruRU', '"I am immune to your charms, outsider. Flattery will get you nowhere."$b$bLord Gravesbane held the princess''s icy glare for one, two, three agonizing seconds, before replying...$b$b|cFF600000<What might Lord Gravesbane say now?>|r', '', 21154),
(110925, 'ruRU', '"That''s a big sword you have there. Are you sure you know how to wield it?"$b$bLord Gravesbane shifted his eyes towards his trousers, then back up at the regal draenei. Matching her hidden half-smile, he replied...$b$b|cFF600000<What might Lord Gravesbane say now?>|r', '', 21154),
(110926, 'ruRU', '"Is that a gnome in your legplates, or is that two gnomes in your legplates?"$b$bLord Gravesbane stumbled backwards, clearly caught off-guard by the directness of the princess''s question. He quickly re-gathered his wits and replied...$b$b|cFF600000<What might Lord Gravesbane say now?>|r', '', 21154),
(110927, 'ruRU', 'I see you carry Felo''melorn, mage. My father spoke of that blade. He witnessed its fire during the War of the Ancients, long before the exodus of the quel''dorei.', '', 21154),
(110928, 'ruRU', '<Wounded guy on the ground. Heal them up.>', '<Wounded guy on the ground. Heal them up.>', 21154),
(110929, 'ruRU', '<The adventurer has broken their arm. If you knew how to set bones, you could treat him.>', '<The adventurer has broken their arm. If you knew how to set bones, you could treat her>', 21154),
(110930, 'ruRU', '"I''ll bet you say that to every princess you meet."$b$bLord Gravesbane could see her for what she really was now: yes, she was the ruler of an unbeatable warrior nation... but she was also a girl, still trembling under the terrible weight of a crown. He replied...$b$b|cFF600000<What might Lord Gravesbane say now?>|r', '', 21154),
(110931, 'ruRU', '"Simply ''cute''? You''ll have to do better than that, Lord Gravesbane."$b$bLord Gravesbane frowned. "Perhaps I''m simply having an off day", he thought, clearly disappointed with his game.$b$b|cFF600000<What might Lord Gravesbane say to recover?>|r', '', 21154),
(110932, 'ruRU', 'Thanks!', 'Thanks!', 21154),
(110933, 'ruRU', '"Well, I think you''re terribly unclever!"$b$bThe azure-skinned princess put on quite a show of being offended. So much, in fact, that it was clear to Lord Gravesbane that she was bluffing. He saw his chance.$b$b|cFF600000<What might Lord Gravesbane say now?>|r', '', 21154),
(110934, 'ruRU', '"Yes, I say it to nearly every woman I meet. I define my self-worth solely by the quantity of my romantic partners."', '"Yes, I say it to nearly every woman I meet. I define my self-worth solely by the quantity of my romantic partners."', 21154),
(110935, 'ruRU', '"No, your majesty. Only to those princesses with eyes like sapphires in a stormy sea."', '"No, your majesty. Only to the ones with eyes like sapphires."', 21154),
(110936, 'ruRU', '"Like, REALLY cute."', '"Like, REALLY cute."', 21154),
(110937, 'ruRU', '"Pants? Here in my court, we simply wear robes and shoulderpads."', '"Pants? Here in my court, we simply wear robes and shoulderpads."', 21154),
(110938, 'ruRU', '"Why would you say such a stupid thing to me?"', '"Why would you say such a stupid thing to me?"', 21154),
(110939, 'ruRU', '$n, I see you have inherited Felo''melorn. Let us hope it serves you better than it did Prince Kael''thas.', '$n, I see you have inherited Felo''melorn. Let us hope it serves you better than it did Prince Kael''thas.', 21154),
(110940, 'ruRU', '"You insolent buffoon! I should have your head for this!"', '"You insolent buffoon! I should have your head for this!"', 21154),
(110941, 'ruRU', '"Pants? Here in my court, we simply wear robes and shoulderpads."$b$bLord Gravesbane surveyed the throne room chamber, and indeed, every single member of the princess''s court was donned in long, flowing robes, and decorated with large crystalline shoulderpads. Not a single pant was in sight. He replied...$b$b|cFF600000<What might Lord Gravesbane say now?>|r', '', 21154),
(110942, 'ruRU', 'Begone, Mortals! Your kind has no place here!', '', 21154),
(110943, 'ruRU', '"Why would you say such a stupid thing to me?"$b$bLord Gravesbane had been called many things before: foul, lecherous, repugnant, perverted, and occasionally even troggish, but never "stupid". This was new. He replied...$b$b|cFF600000<What might Lord Gravesbane say or do now?>|r', '', 21154),
(110944, 'ruRU', 'You will... pay for this... shaman! You...', '', 21154),
(110945, 'ruRU', '"You insolent buffoon! I should have your head for this!"$b$bA score of angry guards unsheathed as many crystalline swords. The princess was angry. One word from her, and Lord Gravesbane would be sliced to ribbons. He would have to choose his next words very carefully.$b$b|cFF600000<What might Lord Gravesbane say to get out of this one?>|r', '', 21154),
(110946, 'ruRU', '"I would settle for a robe drop, I suppose... but your majesty should definitely keep the shoulderpads ON."', '"I would settle for a robe drop, I suppose... but your majesty should definitely keep the shoulderpads ON."', 21154),
(110947, 'ruRU', '"Umm... duhhhh... Lord Gravesbane?"', '"Umm... duhhhh... Lord Gravesbane?"', 21154),
(110948, 'ruRU', '"But your majesty... why take my head, when you already have my heart?"', '"But your majesty... why take my head, when you already have my heart?"', 21154),
(110949, 'ruRU', '"Yikes! Don''t kill me!"', '"Yikes! Don''t kill me!"', 21154),
(110950, 'ruRU', 'You seek the Idol of the Wild? I will tell you nothing, interloper!', '', 21154),
(110951, 'ruRU', 'His immaculate choice of words had won the princess over. Her hands flew to her chest, as if to stop a beating heart from escaping.$b$b"Oh, Lord Gravesbane!" she exclaimed.', '', 21154),
(110952, 'ruRU', '|cFF600000<This story doesn''t seem to be working out so well. It''s not very steamy, and it''s definitely not romantic.>|r', '', 21154),
(110953, 'ruRU', 'Even your sacred shrines are no longer safe from us, druid!', '', 21154),
(110954, 'ruRU', 'I know nothing of this idol, foolish druid. I do know that I''ll have your head!', '', 21154),
(110955, 'ruRU', 'My liege! A strange mage approaches, and $ghe:she; bears the flaming blade of Dath''Remar Sunstrider.', '$n, I see you have inherited Felo''melorn. Let us hope it serves you better than it did Prince Kael''thas.', 21154),
(110956, 'ruRU', '<Wounded guy needs help. Heal them up.>', '<Wounded guy needs help. Heal them up.>', 21154),
