(112314, 'ruRU', 'Can you tell me more about Arrexis?', 'Can you tell me more about Arrexis?', 21154),
(112315, 'ruRU', 'Arrexis was a powerful and well known member of the Order of Tirisfal around the First War. I barely spoke to him, busy with my own goals. I knew he wielded Ebonchill. Then, mysteriously, I returned from a long journey and he was gone. His apprentices were gone and any materials and belongings related to him. The other members of the order were very tightlipped, only saying that something horrible had befallen him.\n\nEbonchill was nowhere to be found.', '', 21154),
(112316, 'ruRU', 'From my findings I believe Arrexis was attempting to build a new warding system against demonic entry. A powerful mage hunting eredar named Balaadur ambushed him during this ritual and probably took the staff for his own.', 'From my findings I believe Arrexis was attempting to build a new warding system against demonic entry. A powerful mage hunting eredar named Balaadur ambushed him during this ritual and probably took the staff for his own.', 21154),
(112317, 'ruRU', 'This is most unsettling! I was so busy I never thought...', '', 21154),
(112318, 'ruRU', 'My staff... in the hands of the enemy! We must get it back!', '', 21154),
(112319, 'ruRU', 'Well done! Now we can begin our counter attack!', '', 21154),
(112320, 'ruRU', 'Poisons. Poisons, here! Family owned and operated since our untimely death.', '', 21154),
(112321, 'ruRU', 'So it is true. You carry with you Anguish and Sorrow, the twin blades that once slit the throat of the Alliance King.$b$bI consider myself an aficionado of poisoned blades, $n. May I see them a moment? I can tell you a little about their history...', '', 21154),
(112322, 'ruRU', 'Ahh, yes. Daggers. The weapon of choice for skilled assassins. Easily concealed, leaving no chance of the victim surviving. Some prefer stiletto blades, for rapid piercing of the victim''s vitals.', '', 21154),
(112323, 'ruRU', 'But Garona, she preferred short, curved blades. They allow one to draw the weapon from the scabbard and slice the target''s throat in a single, deadly motion. Oh, glorious!', '', 21154),
(112324, 'ruRU', 'Note the serrated reverse edge, allowing the wielder to cut back if the first slice misses. Not that Garona ever missed. Her victims were dead before they hit the ground. These are truly a treasure, $n - thank you.', '', 21154),
(112325, 'ruRU', '$n! Come closer. There are rumors about those daggers of yours...', '', 21154),
(112326, 'ruRU', 'With the invasion I have no doubt he is either here or watching. I propose something... audacious.', '', 21154),
(112327, 'ruRU', 'Let us recreate Arrexis''s ritual! If we start the ritual at an invasion point, that will attract Balaadur''s attention. He will likely attempt to ambush the main caster but we will be ready.', '', 21154),
(112328, 'ruRU', 'That just might work. We will need information on this ritual and the power to pull it off. Let us get to it.', '', 21154),
(112329, 'ruRU', '', 'Excellent! Now that we have the key, the way to the balcony should be open. We''re counting on you!', 21154),
(112330, 'ruRU', '', 'When you first set foot upon our shores, I prayed to the spirits asking if you could be trusted. By helping to reunite our tribes, you have proven yourself a true friend to our people.', 21154),
(112331, 'ruRU', '', 'On behalf of the tribes of Highmountain, I entrust the hammer to you and your allies. May it strike true at the heart of the enemy!', 21154),
(112332, 'ruRU', '', 'The spirits whisper that our fates our intertwined, $n. My people stand ready to aid you in the war against the Legion.', 21154),
(112333, 'ruRU', 'Any information you can find on Arrexis, how he died, and where Ebonchill is would be greatly appreciated.', '', 21154),
(112334, 'ruRU', '', 'For us, the Hammer of Khaz''garoth has always been a symbol of unity, a reminder of our proud history. But in your hands, it will serve an even greater purpose.', 21154),
(112335, 'ruRU', 'You will need to speak to the manager at the Bank of Dalaran to gain access. I have cast a sigil on you that should give you permission. Also there might still be personal wards up inside. They shouldn''t harm you but be careful.', '', 21154),
